The North-East Development Commission has donated two ambulances, medical equipment and one transformer to the Adamawa State Government in a bid to help stop the spread of COVID-19 in the country. NEDC also presented food items and condiments to the government to be distributed to residents of the state. Director of Internal Audit at NEDC, Yerima Gashiye, who represented the Managing Director, Mohammed Goni Alkali, said the commission was partnering governments in the North-East region to stop the spread of Coronavirus. The NEDC had earlier provided the state government with 1,000 Personal protective equipment, two ventilators and other medical items. 